   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born in 1315, in Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Robert De Walford in 1334, in Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons."},"et":{"1315–":"1315–Surnud","1313–Male":"1313–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1337–Male":"1337–Surnud","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1334":"1334","1400":"1400","1340":"1340","Walford, Shropshire, England":"Walford, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1315–":"1315–Kuollut","1313–Male":"1313–Kuollut","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1337–Male":"1337–Kuollut","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1334":"1334","1400":"1400","1340":"1340","Walford, Shropshire, England":"Walford, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1315–":"1315–Décédée","1313–Male":"1313–Décédé","1335–Male":"1335–Décédé","1337–Male":"1337–Décédé","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1315–Female":"1315–Décédée","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1334":"1334","1400":"1400","1340":"1340","Walford, Shropshire, England":"Walford, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Agnes est née en 1315, à Walford, Shrops